Overview:-
Hibernate follows a structured workflow to interact with a relational database. It acts as a bridge
between Java objects and database tables, handling object persistence, transactions, and queries
efficiently.

Hibernate Workflow Steps:-
1️⃣ Java Object (POJO) → Hibernate Configuration
2️⃣ SessionFactory Initialization
3️⃣ Session Creation
4️⃣ Transaction Handling
5️⃣ Query Execution (HQL/Criteria API/SQL)
6️⃣ Object Mapping & Data Persistence
7️⃣ Transaction Commit & Session Closing

Complete Hibernate Workflow:-
Java POJO ↔ Hibernate ORM ↔ SQL Query ↔ Database
-----------------------------------------------
1. Define Entity Class (@Entity)
2. Configure Hibernate (hibernate.cfg.xml)
3. Create SessionFactory (Configuration.buildSessionFactory())
4. Open Session (sessionFactory.openSession())
5. Begin Transaction (session.beginTransaction())
6. Perform Database Operation (session.save/update/delete)
7. Commit Transaction (transaction.commit())
8. Close Session (session.close())
